# 2p_frag_charge — HOST (slot 0, left). M6 ship-prep.
#
# Hold-to-charge throw demo + duel. Host and client both spawn on
# Aurora's long flat central floor (cols 50–73, y=2752 floor). Host
# at x=1600, client at x=2200 — 600 px gap so both mechs read
# clearly in each viewport at 1600×900 windowed.
#
# Both throw frag grenades at the other to demonstrate parabolic
# physics: the lob bias rotates the launch up, 1.8× gravity brings
# the grenade down on the target. Throws are staggered so both
# viewports show incoming and outgoing arcs in the same shot. Shot
# names are SHARED with the client script so the runner can paste
# them side-by-side.
#
# Throw schedule (script ticks; world ticks lag ~60 due to lobby +
# countdown elapsing before MATCH starts):
#   Host    @ t=210 → 240    (30 t = 0.50 s hold → medium charge)
#   Client  @ t=260 → 320    (60 t = 1.00 s hold → max charge)
#   Host    @ t=380 → 440    (60 t = 1.00 s hold → max charge)
#   Client  @ t=480 → 510    (30 t = 0.50 s hold → medium charge)
#
# 1.5 s fuse = 90 ticks; world-tick offset for booms:
#   throw 1 boom ≈ script 330   (host's medium lands ~midpoint)
#   throw 2 boom ≈ script 345   (client's max lands ~at host)
#   throw 3 boom ≈ script 530   (host's max overshoots client)
#   throw 4 boom ≈ script 595   (client's medium lands ~midpoint)

window 1600 900
out build/shots/net/2p_frag_charge_host
network host 24310
name HostA
map aurora

loadout - "Pulse Rifle" "Frag Grenades" Light Standard

spawn_at 1600 2712
peer_spawn 1 2200 2712

aim 2200 2702

# Swap to secondary so LMB → throw.
at 130 press swap
at 138 release swap

# Throw 1 — medium charge → toward client B.
at 210 press fire
at 240 release fire

# Throw 2 — max charge → toward client B again.
at 380 press fire
at 440 release fire

# === SHARED-NAME CAPTURES ===
# (Names describe the world event so host + client snapshots line up
# in the side-by-side composite.)

at 150 shot t150_idle
at 180 shot t180_post_swap

# Throw 1 (host medium): meter visible, launch, arc, descent, boom.
at 230 shot t230_throw1_charging
at 250 shot t250_throw1_launch
at 270 shot t270_throw1_apex
at 300 shot t300_throw1_descent
at 330 shot t330_throw1_boom

# Throw 2 (client max): client charging, launch, arc, boom.
at 290 shot t290_throw2_charging
at 320 shot t320_throw2_launch
at 345 shot t345_throw2_apex_boom

# Throw 3 (host max): long arc across the gap.
at 430 shot t430_throw3_charging
at 460 shot t460_throw3_launch
at 500 shot t500_throw3_apex
at 535 shot t535_throw3_boom

# Throw 4 (client medium): short lob back.
at 510 shot t510_throw4_launch
at 560 shot t560_throw4_arc
at 595 shot t595_throw4_boom

at 660 shot t660_done

contact_sheet host_sheet cols 4

at 720 end
